For compiling the vmm manager ko module

-- SETTING UP ENVIRONMENT --

1. Download a linux kernal archive,
	the one used and tested with these instructions is: https://www.kernel.org/pub/linux/kernel/v3.x/linux-3.15.1.tar.gz

2. Extract the archive into linux/build/driver_module

3. Move the .config file located in this directory into the head directory of the kernel archive (e.g. linux/build/driver_module/linux-3.15.1/)

4. In the linux/build/driver_module makefile, set KHEAD to be the name of the head kernel directory

5. In the top level makefile for the linux kernel, change the version magic number to:

VERSION = 3
PATCHLEVEL = 15
SUBLEVEL = 0
EXTRAVERSION =
NAME = Shuffling Zombie Juror

6. Run the following commands in the kernel archive

make oldconfig
make prepare
make modules_prepare

-- BUILDING KERNEL MODULE --

Run the makefile in linux/build/driver_module to build the vmm_manager.ko
